                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002 Manchuria/157: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-08T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 8, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 8—3:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>782. Following from American Consul General at Harbin: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 7, 3 p.m. <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_OEJ1"
                                >Ohrnberger</persName>, deputy commissioner, and <persName
                                corresp="frus1932v03#p_RTM1">Rozoff</persName>, assistant in the
                            customs, arrested by the Manchukuo police early this afternoon and raid
                            now taking place Commissioner’s residence where some Chinese employees
                            customs had taken refuge.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
